#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:0.4"
msgid "Attakā­ma­pāri­cari­ya­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "4. The training rule on fulfilling one’s own desires"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.132, pts-vp-en1.222, pts-cs-bu-ss4.1.1, ms1V_1180 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anātha­piṇḍi­kassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī sāvatthiyaṃ kulūpako hoti, bahukāni kulāni upasaṅkamati."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī was associating with and visiting a number of families in Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā itthī matapatikā abhirūpā hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī pubbaṇ­ha­samayaṃ nivāsetvā patta­cīvara­mādāya yena tassā itthiyā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "One morning Udāyī robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to the house of a beautiful widow,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on the prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.6"
msgid "Atha kho sā itthī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "That woman approached Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.8"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ itthiṃ āyasmā udāyī dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr "Udāyī then instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.9"
msgid "Atha kho sā itthī āyasmatā udāyinā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And she said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.10"
msgid "“vadeyyātha, bhante, yena attho."
msgstr "“Venerable, please say what you need."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.11"
msgid "Paṭibalā mayaṃ ayyassa dātuṃ yadidaṃ cīvara­piṇḍa­pāta­se­nāsa­na­gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khā­ran”ti."
msgstr "I’m able to give robe-cloth, almsfood, a dwelling, and medicines.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_1181 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.12"
msgid "“Na kho te, bhagini, amhākaṃ dullabhā yadidaṃ cīvara­piṇḍa­pāta­se­nāsa­na­gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khārā."
msgstr "“It’s not hard for us, Sister, to get those requisites."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.13"
msgid "Api ca yo amhākaṃ dullabho taṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "Give instead what’s hard for us to get.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.14"
msgid "“Kiṃ, bhante”ti?"
msgstr "“What’s that, Venerable?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.15"
msgid "“Methunadhamman”ti."
msgstr "“Sexual intercourse.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.16"
msgid "“Attho, bhante”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it wanted now, Venerable?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.17"
msgid "“Attho, bhaginī”ti."
msgstr "“It is, Sister.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.223
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.18"
msgid "“Ehi, bhante”ti,"
msgstr "“Come, Venerable,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.19"
msgid "ovarakaṃ pavisitvā sāṭakaṃ nikkhipitvā mañcake uttānā nipajji."
msgstr "and she entered her bedroom, took off her clothes, and lay back on the bed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.20"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā—"
msgstr "Udāyī approached her and spat out,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.21"
msgid "“ko imaṃ vasalaṃ duggandhaṃ āmasissatī”ti,"
msgstr "“Who would touch this foul-smelling wretch!”"

#. VAR: niṭṭhubhitvā → nuṭṭhuhitvā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.22"
msgid "niṭṭhubhitvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "and he departed."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_1182 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.23"
msgid "Atha kho sā itthī ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "That woman then complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.24"
msgid "“alajjino ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dussīlā musāvādino."
msgstr "“These Sakyan recluses are shameless and immoral liars."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.25"
msgid "Ime hi nāma dhammacārino samacārino brahmacārino saccavādino sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā paṭijānissanti."
msgstr "They claim to live according to the Truth, to be celibate and of good conduct, to be truthful, moral, and of good character."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.26"
msgid "Natthi imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ natthi imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, kuto imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ kuto imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ,"
msgstr "But they don’t have the qualities of an ascetic or a brahmin;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.27"
msgid "apagatā ime sāmaññā apagatā ime brahmaññā."
msgstr "they’ve lost the plot."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.28"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma samaṇo udāyī maṃ sāmaṃ methunadhammaṃ yācitvā, ‘ko imaṃ vasalaṃ duggandhaṃ āmasissatī’ti niṭṭhubhitvā pakkamissati."
msgstr "How can the ascetic Udāyī request sexual intercourse from me, but then spit out, ‘Who would touch this foul-smelling wretch!’ and depart?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.29"
msgid "Kiṃ me pāpakaṃ kiṃ me duggandhaṃ,"
msgstr "What’s bad about me? How am I foul-smelling?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.1.30"
msgid "kassāhaṃ kena hāyāmī”ti?"
msgstr "In what way am I inferior to whom?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_1183, pts-cs-bu-ss4.1.2, ms1V_1184 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.1"
msgid "Aññāpi itthiyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "Other women, too, criticized him"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.2"
msgid "“alajjino ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dussīlā musāvādino … pe …"
msgstr "in the same way,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.3"
msgid "kathañhi nāma samaṇo udāyī imissā sāmaṃ methunadhammaṃ yācitvā, ‘ko imaṃ vasalaṃ duggandhaṃ āmasissatī’ti niṭṭhubhitvā pakkamissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.4"
msgid "Kiṃ imissā pāpakaṃ kiṃ imissā duggandhaṃ, kassāyaṃ kena hāyatī”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.5"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ itthīnaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ."
msgstr "and the monks heard them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.224
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī mātugāmassa santike attakā­ma­pāri­cari­yāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī commend the fulfilling of his own desires in the presence of a woman?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato → atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato (sī1, syā1-3, pā1)
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-pli3.133, ms1V_1185
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.9"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "Those monks rebuked Udāyī in many ways and then told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.10"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.11"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, mātugāmassa santike attakā­ma­pāri­cari­yāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you commended the fulfilling of your own desires in the presence of a woman?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.12"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.13"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.14"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“It’s not suitable, foolish man, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a recluse, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.15"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmassa santike attakā­ma­pāri­cari­yāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissasi."
msgstr "How can you commend the fulfilling of your own desires in the presence of a woman?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.16"
msgid "Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito no sarāgāya … pe …"
msgstr "Haven’t I given many teachings for the sake of dispassion, not for the sake of passion …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.17"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto?"
msgstr "for the stilling of the fevers of sense desire?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_1186
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.20"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena mātugāmassa santike attakā­ma­pāri­cari­yāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyya—"
msgstr "‘If a lustful monk encourages a woman to satisfy his own needs:"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.225
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:1.2.21"
msgid "‘etadaggaṃ, bhagini, pāricariyānaṃ yā mādisaṃ sīlavantaṃ kalyāṇadhammaṃ brahmacāriṃ etena dhammena paricareyyāti methunu­pasaṃ­hi­tena’, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "“Sister, she provides the highest service who in this way satisfies one like me, who is virtuous, celibate, and of good character,” and if it is a reference to sexual intercourse, he commits an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-ss4.2, ms1V_1187
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_1188
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.6"
msgid "Otiṇṇo nāma"
msgstr "Lustful:"

# NOTE: I have rendered _otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena_ with the single word “lustful.” This means that the definition for _vipariṇataṃ_ is missing from my translation. Here is the Pali, followed by a translation: _Vipariṇatanti rattampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Duṭṭhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Mūḷhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Api ca rattaṃ cittaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetaṃ vipariṇatanti_; “distorted: a mind with desire is distorted, a mind with anger is distorted, a confused mind is distorted. But in this case ‘distorted’ refers to a mind with desire.”
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.7"
msgid "sāratto apekkhavā paṭi­baddha­citto."
msgstr "having lust, longing for, in love with."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_1189
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:2.8"
msgid "Vipariṇatanti"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
